        "title": "Hypokalemia and Membrane Hyperpolarization",
        "definition": "Reduced extracellular potassium hyperpolarizes resting membrane potential, decreasing excitability in skeletal muscle and cardiac tissue.",
        "summary": "Low [K+]o increases K+ equilibrium potential magnitude, making cells harder to depolarize to threshold. ECG changes reflect cardiac effects."
      },
